- Low elevation (below 1000 m), gentle slope angle (below 30 degrees), and southerly aspect angle (below 60 degrees) are more commonly associated with valley locations.
- Intermediate elevation (1000-1500 m), moderate slope angle (30-40 degrees), and southerly to easterly aspect angle (30-60 degrees) are more commonly associated with plateau locations.

## Task Assumptions
- The assistant may use a machine learning model or a rule-based approach to predict the trailhead location.
- The assistant may consider the following general guidelines for topographic features:
  - Mountain: Elevation > 1500 m, Slope angle > 40 degrees, Aspect angle > 60 degrees.
  - Valley: Elevation < 1000 m, Slope angle < 30 degrees, Aspect angle < 60 degrees.
  - Plateau: 1000-1500 m elevation, 30-40 degrees slope angle, 30-60 degrees aspect angle.

